      {
        heading: "📚 Topic 2 Key Vocabulary",
        type: "vocab",
        content: `<div class="ls-vocab-grid">
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Brain plasticity</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">The brain's ability to modify and form new neural pathways in response to experience and learning.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Developmental plasticity</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">High plasticity in infants and children — rapid neural pathway formation and consolidation.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Adaptive plasticity</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Ongoing plasticity across the lifespan enabling lifelong learning and recovery from injury.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Proliferation</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">First stage of brain development: rapid cell division producing neurons (250,000/min).</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Migration</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Newly formed neurons travel to their final brain location, where they specialise.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Synaptogenesis</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Formation of new synapses during circuit formation (third developmental stage).</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Synaptic pruning</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Elimination of unused or weak neural connections to increase efficiency. 'Use it or lose it.'</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Myelination</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Formation of fatty myelin sheath around axons, speeding signal transmission. Last stage of brain maturation.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Critical period</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">A time window during which specific experiences MUST occur for normal development.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Sensitive period</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">An optimal time for learning particular skills; development is possible but harder outside this window.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Experience-expectant</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Development that depends on specific experiences during a critical/sensitive period.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Experience-dependent</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Learning that can occur at any point in life from unique individual experiences.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Attachment</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">The emotional bond between infant and caregiver; foundation for all future relationships.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Privation</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Never forming an attachment bond — more severe than deprivation.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Deprivation</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Loss of an existing attachment after a bond has been formed.</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Schema</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">A mental framework organising knowledge and experience (Piaget).</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Assimilation</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Fitting new experiences into an existing schema without changing it (Piaget).</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Accommodation</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Modifying or creating a new schema when new information doesn't fit (Piaget).</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">ZPD</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Zone of Proximal Development — gap between independent and assisted performance (Vygotsky).</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Scaffolding</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Temporary support from a more knowledgeable other to help a learner master a task (Vygotsky).</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Processing speed</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">How quickly the brain can perform a cognitive task — increases with age (IPT).</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Cognitive strategies</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Mental strategies used to solve problems — refined with development (IPT).</div></div>
          <div class="ls-vocab-card"><div class="ls-vocab-term">Metacognition</div><div class="ls-vocab-def">Awareness and understanding of one's own thinking processes — 'thinking about thinking' (IPT).</div></div>
        </div>`
      }
